parameters.name: SPACECRAFT EVENT TIME (UT)
parameters.description:
Spacecraft event time (UT) given in PDS standard time format            
      (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ).

parameters.name: GLL_R
parameters.description:
Spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in units of Rj         
      where Rj = 71492 km.

parameters.name: GLL_S3_LAT
parameters.description: Spacecraft System III (1965.0) latitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: GLL_S3_LON
parameters.description: Spacecraft System III (1965.0) West longitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: GLL_SOLAR_PHASE_ANGLE
parameters.description:
Spacecraft solar phase angle, measured couterclockwise from the         
      Sun-Jupiter anti-solar line in the jovian equatorial plane.

parameters.name: GLL_EARTH_PHASE_ANGLE
parameters.description:
Spacecraft Earth phase angle, measured couterclockwise from the         
      Earth-Jupiter anti-earthward line in the jovian equatorial plane.
